decision_conditions:
WHEELCHAIR HOUSING (COMPLIANCE:  The 12 wheelchair/wheelchair adaptable dwellings, shall meet the requirements of part M4(3) of the Building Regulations in in accordance with the Design and Access Statement and plans hereby approved, and be permanently retained as such, and shall be provided prior to the first occupation of the development.  

REASON:  To secure provision of the appropriate number of wheelchair accessible units in a timely fashion and to: address the backlog of and current unmet accommodation needs; produce a sustainable mix of accommodation; and provide appropriate choices and housing opportunities for wheelchair users and their families.
description: Redevelopment of site to provide 118 residential units in buildings ranging from 3 to 6 storeys in height, accessible car parking, cycle parking, landscaping and other associated development
